  "description": [
    "STOCKS HAVE DULL SESSION Market Enjoys Strong Opening but Interest k Rapidly Disappears f CALL MONEY ADVANCES High Money Rate Forces Selling in All Speculative Issues New Tork July IIWall Street had another bad day in the tock market with call money renewing at 8 per cent ttd lending aa high 1 as 11 Many of the most venturesome speculators of the street were at the yacht race In the afternoon so that business was small less than 500000 shares being done all dayThe opening was fairly strong but selling began almost immediately By 1 oclock per cent was bid for 15000000 on the exchange and no money forthcoming When the rate moved to 11 per cent selling was forced in all the speculative Issues Stromberg and Crucible fared worst but the whole list suffered rather severely United States Steel and other standard issues made new low records for the movement steel touching 91 The closing was at about the worst prices In all the issues Because Germany yielded on the question of coal and made occupation of the Ruhr district by the allies unnecessary a good many traders expected a rally in the market Announcement that a committee of"
